<FLAG>In brief</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974995458</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SEVERAL Government Ministers have become victims of car or mobile phone cloning
in the past 18 months it was disclosed last night. The illegal practice, by
which numbers are obtained and then transferred to other mobile phones so calls
can be made free of charge and billed to the original owner, is prevalent in
central London. A series of written replies to Labour's Brian Donohoe
(Cunnnghame South) gave the extent of cloning in Government departments. It was
said to have happened once to Scottish Secretary Michael Forsyth - when he was
serving as a Home Office Minister.
</TEXT>
