<HEADLINE>Sports awards</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>40</PAGE>
<FLAG>SPORT</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974995459</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE unstinting service of five of Scotland's leading sports volunteers was
recognised last night in a ceremony at Murrayfield, Edinburgh, where Raymond
Robertson, the Scottish Office Minister with responsibility for sport, made the
Scottish Sports Council National Service to Sport presentations.
Anne Gulland has served Scottish and UK hockey for almost 50 years, and steps
down after 19 years as treasurer of GB women following next year's Olympics.
Mac Henderson was a Scottish junior badminton internationalist in the early
1950s, played in the 1966 Commonwealth Games, and is still on the management
board of the Scottish Badminton Union of which he has been treasurer for the
past 12 years. Dennis Carmichael, honorary president of the Scottish Lawn
Tennis Association is the only Scot to become chairman of the LTA (1978), while
Jack Richmond and George Stewart have given notable service to shinty and
skiing respectively.
</TEXT>
