<HEADLINE>Taking first step on road to glory</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>Mike Hagerty</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>40</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974995465</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AT six locations stretching from Aberdeen to Stranraer, 42 teams take to the
ice this weekend, aiming to qualify for the next stage of the season's premier
domestic event, the Maccallan Scottish champion-ships.
The Aberdeen line-up includes the Perth team of Warwick, David, and Peter
Smith, and lead player David Hay who, following their latest victory in last
week's Edinburgh International, are among the favourites to take the title
overall next year.
They open their campaign this evening against John Jo Kenny, who made it all
the way to the national finals in Perth last season.
Tom Brewster, the current world junior champion, leads the line-up on his home
ice in Lockerbie, while at Murrayfield, the Scottish champion of two seasons
ago, Colin Hamilton, is in action against Alex MacGregor this evening.
The top teams from last year's national finals have been exempted from
participation at this stage of the championships this year, but even without
the likes of European champion Hammy McMillan and defending Scottish champion
Gordon Muirhead, there is still the prospect of keen competition and quality
play over the weekend to come.
Summit Centre, Glasgow. Women's Frank Stuart Final - C Marshall 7, P Thomson 6.
MIKE HAGGERTY
</TEXT>
