<DATE>951208</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Escom expands Scottish operation</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>25</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974995470</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ESCOM, the German computer company which has a factory in Irvine, opened three
more computer shops in Scotland yesterday.
The retail outlets in Glasgow, Dundee, and and Inverness are in addition to two
existing shops in Glasgow. Escom has rapidly expanded its UK retail network
this year.
Following the purchase of the Rumbelow chain in March and the opening of 100
new stores in May, it now operates over 200 shops. A further 50 concessions in
out-of-town Office World shops are due to open in February.
Escom hopes to raise its share of the UK personal computer market to 10% next
year from an estimated 7% at present. Its factory in Irvine opened in 1993 and
employs 300 people.
</TEXT>
