<DATE>951208</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Volleyball</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>40</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974995505</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FRENCH side UC Paris have had their perparations for this weekend's European
Confederation Cup in Glasgow thrown into chaos by the French public transport
strike.
The French, who include the legendary Alain Fabiani in their ranks, finally
arrived in Glasgow yesterday - 21 hours after setting out for the airport. They
had planned to fly straight to Glasgow, but had to stay overnight in Birmingham
on Wednesday.
Paris open the tournament at the Kelvin Hall against Croatians Osijec tonight
at 5pm with Scottish champions City of Glasgow Ragazzi facing Balkancar Sofia
at 7.30.
</TEXT>
