<DATE>951208</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Three guilty of killing Briton</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974995545</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Nairobi, Thursday
THREE Kenyan High Court Assessors have returned a unanimous guilty verdict
against three men charged with the rape and murder of Briton Caron Winter.
Under Kenyan law, while the Assessors verdict is regarded as crucial, the trial
judge is not bound to agree with their decision.
Yusuf Rashid Wamasoro, alias ``Toto'', James Washikomba, and Alexander
Eshikavale had earlier denied raping and murdering the 31-year-old housewife
after forcing their way into the Winters' home in June last year.
If convicted of charge all three face a mandatory death sentence.
The prosecution alleged the men took turns raping Caron Winter before hacking
her to death. Her 11-month-old baby survived unharmed.
Husband Adam Winter was beaten unconscious by the attackers after surprising
them when he returned home for lunch.
Judge Samuel Bosire ordered the accused to remain in Kamiti maximum security
jail until he delivers a final verdict on December 13.
RIO DE JANEIRO: A woman was trampled to death at the Maracana stadium in Rio de
Janeiro before the South American Supercup final between Flamengo and
Independiente.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
