<TEXT>
KEVIN McKenzie, Stirling County's international hooker, returns to rugby
tomorrow.
The Scottish champions have recalled him for the regional league match against
Kilmarnock at Bridgehaugh, his first game since he damaged knee ligaments in
the premiership game against Melrose at the Greenyards nine weeks ago.
McKenzie, though, is among only a handful of first-choice players in the team.
County, like other senior clubs, have been denuded by district calls for the
start of the new phase in Scottish rugby, the regional leagues which will
decided the seeding positions in the cup competition.
It is, however, the opportunity for younger players to come through. Grant
Macfarlane, the former Scottish Schools cap who made his debut for Glasgow in
the under-21 district championship win over North and Midlands on Wednesday,
has been enlisted by West of Scotland to replace Guy Perrett against Ayr at
Millbrae, and a more recent schools international player, Andrew Dall is to
