<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974995582</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Stirling and
Ayr in the
Grand tour
THE new roving Scottish Grand Committee is to meet next month in the Stirling
constituency of Scottish Secretary Michael Forsyth, and in another Tory
marginal, Ayr, at Labour's suggestion, writes Stuart Trotter.
The Opposition has decided that the committee of all Scotland's MPs which Mr
Forsyth proposed should meet at more venues in Scotland, should move into
vulnerable Tory areas.
The Ayr visit will be an evidence-taking session before MPs begin detailed
consideration of a Bill giving local authorities more powers over the holding
of rave parties.
</TEXT>
